31/10/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The Greek Orthodox Ecumenical Patriarch Vartholomeos protested Sunday (30 October) the actions of Turkish nationalists against the Ecumenical Patriarchate in Istanbul last week.
Some 200 Turkish nationalist demonstrators marched in Istanbul, demanding the relocation of the Patriarchate from Turkey to Greece.
In other news, tests of samples conducted in a British laboratory found no trace of bird flu in Greece, the country's agriculture ministry announced on Saturday.
The government immediately lifted restrictions it had imposed on the islands of Chios and Oinousses, where dead birds had been found.
(ANA - 30/10/05;
Reuters, AP, AFP - 29/10/05)
